🛡️ 📋 Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist
✔️ General Safety Tips
Use strong and unique passwords for all accounts
Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) wherever possible
Do not click on suspicious links or unknown attachments
Verify the authenticity of emails, messages, and websites
Avoid sharing personal information on public platforms
Keep your devices and apps updated regularly
Use secure and trusted Wi-Fi networks (avoid public Wi-Fi for sensitive tasks)
Log out from accounts when using shared or public devices
💰 Financial / UPI Safety Tips
Never share your UPI PIN, OTP, or banking details with anyone
Remember: entering your UPI PIN means you are sending money, not receiving it
Double-check payment requests before approving transactions
Use official apps only (Google Pay, PhonePe, Paytm, etc.)
🚨 Reporting Cybercrime
Report incidents at: https://cybercrime.gov.in
Call Cyber Crime Helpline: 1930 (24x7)
